{"title": "Going against the grain: How farmers in Asia, Australia are beating the heat with new crop varieties", "tags": "asia", "timestamp": "2024-08-26", "content": "NEW DELHI - Crops have always been at the mercy of the weather. But climate change is making farming even more of a lottery, with increasingly extreme weather damaging crops, cutting yields and slashing farmers\u2019 incomes.\nAnd increasingly hot and dry weather is especially harmful, affecting the ability of crops such as wheat to grow."}